    },
    {
      "id": "4b903fa7eed10cad852fe604c0087c5fde139407",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 470,
        "name": "Olaf Weber",
        "email": "olaf.weber@hpe.com",
        "username": "olaf"
      },
      "date": "2016-08-19 17:05:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI recall discussing this with Amir. In lnet_rtrpools_alloc() the_lnet.ln_routing is set to 1. The one thing not done is to clear LNET_PING_FEAT_RTE_DISABLED if it has somehow been set.\n\nThis should be correct for the call from LNetNIInit(), but apparently not for the call from lnet_rtrpools_enable(). You may want to examine the logic surrounding these calls some more.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
